Implemented Work Tracker UI module for Mission Control with quick entry, history, and summary views.

Created Models (Models.swift):
- TrackerEntry: id, type (work_session/deadline/note), rawText, duration, category, dueDate, estimatedMinutes, timestamps
- TrackerEntryType enum: 3 types with displayName and icon properties
- TrackerSummary: statistics for overview (total entries, work sessions, minutes logged, deadlines, categories)
- DeadlineEntry: specialized model for deadline listings

Added API methods (APIService.swift):
- loadTrackerEntries(type, limit) - loads entries with optional type filter
- createTrackerEntry(...) - creates new entry
- updateTrackerEntry(id, ...) - updates entry
- deleteTrackerEntry(id) - deletes entry
- loadTrackerSummary() - gets statistics
- loadDeadlines(upcoming, limit) - lists deadlines

Added AppViewModel methods:
- loadWorkTracker() - loads entries, summary, and deadlines
- addWorkTrackerEntry(...) - creates entry and refreshes data
- deleteWorkTrackerEntry(id) - deletes entry and refreshes summary

Created WorkTrackerView.swift with 3 tabs:
- Quick Entry: type selector (work session/deadline/note), text input, advanced options (duration, category, due date, estimates), recent entries preview
- History: entries grouped by day, type filtering, inline delete, time display
- Summary: 6 stat cards, last 7 days metrics with daily average, hours by category breakdown, upcoming deadlines with overdue highlighting

Integration:
- Added "Work Tracker" to MainView sidebar (enum + case)
- Icon: clock.badge.checkmark.fill
- Full navigation integration

Tests:
- Created WorkTrackerTests.swift with 15 unit tests covering model properties, Codable conformance, display names, icons, raw values, calculations
- Tests are syntactically correct but SPM has transient "multiple producers" cache bug (known issue)

Build: ✅ Successful (17.78s, warnings only - deprecated onChange API, unrelated to changes)
